## Why This Is Asked
Real-world BI workloads multiplex dozens to thousands of tenants; CKNE-driven concurrency and memory control is critical for SLOs and fair sharing.

## Key Concepts
- CKNE-to-resource mapping: concurrency, memory budget, spill/IO throttling
- Per-tenant quotas and dynamic reallocation cadence
- Fairness guarantees and explicit preemption rules
- Telemetry hooks and feedback for regret-free adjustment

## Code Example
```javascript
function allocate(tenants){
  // normalize CKNE 0-1 to weight, compute quotas
  const total = tenants.reduce((a,t)=>a+t.ckne,0);
  tenants.forEach(t=>{ t.alloc = t.ckne/total; });
  return tenants;
}
```

